Kiki Dee (born Pauline Matthews, 6 March 1947, Little Horton, Bradford, West Yorkshire, England[1]) is a successful singer-songwriter, with a career that has lasted over 40 years.

Her most famous song was a duet with Elton John, entitled "Don&#039;t Go Breaking My Heart", which was released in 1976 and went to Number 1 both in the UK Singles Chart and the U.S. Billboard Hot 100 chart. In 1993 she performed another duet with Elton John for his Duets album, a cover version of Cole Porter&#039;s "True Love", which reached #2 in the UK.

I&#039;ve Got the Music in Me by The Kiki Dee Band was released in 1974. It was written in 1973 by Bias Boshell, The Kiki Dee Band&#039;s keyboard player.

The song entered the charts on September 7, reached number 19 and stayed in the charts for eight weeks.
